# Step 4 Is Well Posed Because Two Candidates Are Stable After Canonicalization And The Third Remains An Honest Admission Filter

Status: `VERIFIED` Step-4 readiness verdict with `INFERRED` candidate hierarchy

The completed Step-3 robustness audit leaves Chain Step 4 well posed.
No promoted candidate was killed at the true exact-symmetry tier:
`Template-Defect Near-Closure` and `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget`
survive as `stable after canonicalization`, while
`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` survives as `use-case-limited but honest`.

This yields a clear Step-4 hierarchy.
`Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` is the primary robust obstruction-facing
gate, `Template-Defect Near-Closure` is the primary theorem-facing
role-template gate, and `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` should stay a narrow
pro-near-circuit admission filter rather than a coercive theorem observable.

Step 4 should therefore work only with explicit pro-circuit and anti-circuit
packet families on the frozen packet sheets, windows, class partitions,
thresholds, sign / phase data, and defect or leakage tolerances rather than
retuning them after outcomes are seen.

